{"turn": 8, "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"in": 2, "out": 2274, "cache_read": 10798, "cache_write": 681}, "blocks": [{"signature": "", "thinking": "", "type": "thinking"}, {"text": "# Executive Summary \u2014 Spring Glow Creative Campaign\n\n## Overview\n\"Campaign Spring Glow\" is Lumina Beauty Corp's launch strategy for the hero product **GlowSerum**, built around the core message *\"Reawakening Your Natural Radiance\"* and targeting a 25% uplift in unit sales within six weeks of launch (Source: `brief.txt`, memo from Sarah Chen, VP of Marketing Strategy, dated Oct 26 2023). The initiative is tracked internally under the code **SGX (Spring Glow Campaign Execution)**.\n\n## Total Spend\nSpend figures for Spring Glow appear across two distinct budget records, and internal correspondence flags that these figures are **not fully reconciled**:\n\n- **`spring_glow_budget.csv`** (creative-specific budget breakdown) lists:\n  - Media: AUD 25,000\n  - Production: AUD 15,000\n  - Agency: AUD 8,000\n  - Talent: AUD 5,000\n  - Printing: AUD 1,200\n  - **Subtotal: AUD 54,200**\n\n- **`memo_0778_234.md`** (Marco Nguyen, Campaign Manager, Feb 7 2026) states a **total SGX budget of AUD 385,000**, split into:\n  - Creative production: AUD 120,000\n  - Digital media: AUD 150,000\n  - Audience research/analytics: AUD 115,000\n\n- A separate internal email (`email_1354_865.txt`) reports spend at **87% of the approved budget** as the campaign entered its final stages, without restating the absolute figure.\n\n- **Caution/gap noted in source data:** An internal email from Isla Carmichael (`email_0165_770.eml` / `_v1.eml`, Dec 9 2025) explicitly flags **\"unaggregated spend across Spring Glow creative campaigns\"** and requests the finance team cross-check the numbers during an internal review \u2014 indicating the company's own records do not yet have a single verified total.\n\n**Conclusion on spend:** The documented creative production line item is **AUD 120,000** (per the SGX master budget memo), against a total campaign budget of **AUD 385,000**; a separate, smaller creative-cost worksheet totals **AUD 54,200**. Given the flagged reconciliation issue, this figure should be confirmed with Finance before being cited externally.\n\n## Approved Creative Concepts\n- Final sign-off was granted for **Spring Campaign visual assets**, including **high-resolution imagery and packaging renders** (Source: `creative_approved.eml`, \"Final Sign-off Request: Spring Campaign Visual Assets,\" Oct 26 2023).\n- **TVC (TV commercial) visuals** received internal approval during the campaign's final phase, though minor adjustments were required for color/gradient alignment between the TVC packshot and the approved product design brief (Sources: `status_report_0674_480.md`, `status_report_0674_480_v1.md`, `memo_0764_205.txt`/`_v1.txt`).\n- Concept approvals were scheduled for completion by **2026-02-15** (Source: `memo_0778_234.md`).\n\n## Delivering Team/Agency\n- The **\"Project Zenith\" creative team** produced and requested final sign-off on the visual assets (imagery and packaging renders) (Source: `creative_approved.eml`).\n- **Melbournescope Studios** is referenced as the studio behind the product design brief/TVC packshot and confirmed its availability for concept approvals (Sources: `memo_0778_234.md`, `email_0494_957.txt`).\n- Supporting vendors named across SGX status updates include **Skyline Analytics** and **Dingo Consulting** (campaign alignment), **Sunrise PR** (PR/briefing), and **Red Centre Legal** (contract compliance) \u2014 these appear to be execution/vendor partners rather than the primary creative agency (Sources: `email_0838_244.txt`, `email_0494_957.txt`, `status_report_0674_480.md`).\n\n## Recommendation\nBefore this summary is finalized for external or board use, Finance should reconcile the AUD 54,200 creative-cost worksheet against the AUD 385,000 SGX master budget (AUD 120,000 creative line), per the open item raised in `email_0165_770.eml`.", "type": "text"}]}
